Our work is driven by the following interlinked key goals:
- develop (and distribute) novel usages of mobile tech, in order to help
the public exercise their legal rights while respecting police powers.
- collect (and publish) reliable first-hand data on police actions, to find
the effect of demographic factors including race & class on policing.
The IWITNESS project is a not-for-profit that aims to become the
leading platform for individual & collective justice within Europe.
mock app: BLUE BOOK [1]
launch the WITNESS view
Our core offering is to be the BLUE BOOK application for Android & iOS.
It provides means to record interaction with law enforcement personnel
(like police, border control or immigration officers) while ensuring that:
- this recording functionality may be used with absolute discretion
by temporarily hiding the (running) app from the device user.
- metadata including GPS location is also collected when available.
- the user may unlock the recording, to either continue or finish it,
only after a certain duration (e.g. 60 seconds) has elapsed.
- recorded data is streamed (i.e. continuously uploaded) to our server,
or saved locally for later upload when no data connection is possible.
